# Social Media Post Engagement Analysis

## Project Overview
This project analyzes user reactions on social media posts to measure engagement.  
It counts likes, comments, and shares per post, calculates average reactions per user per day, and identifies the top engaging posts within a timeframe.

## Dataset

### Posts Table

| Column Name   | Data Type          | Description                   |
|---------------|--------------------|-------------------------------|
| post_id       | INTEGER (Primary Key) | Unique identifier for each post |
| post_content  | TEXT               | Content of the post           |
| post_date     | TIMESTAMP          | Date and time the post was made|

### UserReactions Table

| Column Name    | Data Type          | Description                   |
|----------------|--------------------|-------------------------------|
| reaction_id    | INTEGER (Primary Key) | Unique identifier for each reaction |
| user_id        | INTEGER            | Unique identifier for the user|
| post_id        | INTEGER            | Foreign key referencing Posts |
| reaction_type  | VARCHAR(10)        | Type of reaction (like, comment, share) |
| reaction_date  | TIMESTAMP          | Date and time of the reaction |

## SQL Queries

### Create Posts Table and Insert Data
```sql
CREATE TABLE Posts (
    post_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    post_content TEXT,
    post_date TIMESTAMP
);

INSERT INTO Posts (post_id, post_content, post_date) VALUES
(1, 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet', '2023-08-25 10:00:00'),
(2, 'Exploring the beauty of nature', '2023-08-26 15:30:00'),
(3, 'Unveiling the latest tech trends', '2023-08-27 12:00:00'),
(4, 'Journey into the world of literature', '2023-08-28 09:45:00'),
(5, 'Capturing the essence of city life', '2023-08-29 16:20:00');
